    • allgather

      public void allgather(byte[] aSendBuf, int aSendCount, byte[] rRecvBuf, int aRecvCount) throws MPIException
      Gathers data from all members of a group and sends the data to all members of the group. The allgather function is similar to the gather(byte[], int, byte[], int, int) function, except that it sends the data to all processes instead of only to the root. The usage rules for allgather correspond to the rules for gather(byte[], int, byte[], int, int).
      参数:
      aSendBuf - The data array to be sent to all processes in the group. The number of the elements in the buffer are specified in the aSendCount and the data type will be detected automatically. Each element in the buffer corresponds to a process in the group.
      aSendCount - The number of elements in the buffer that is specified in the sendbuf parameter. If sendcount is zero, the data part of the message is empty.
      rRecvBuf - The data array that is received from each process. The number of the elements in the buffer are specified in the aRecvCount parameters and the data type will be detected automatically.
      aRecvCount - The number of elements in the receive buffer. If the count is zero, the data part of the message is empty.
      抛出:
      MPIException

    • allgatherv

      public void allgatherv(byte[] aSendBuf, int aSendCount, byte[] rRecvBuf, int[] aRecvCounts, int[] aDispls) throws MPIException
      Gathers a variable amount of data from each member of a group and sends the data to all members of the group. The allgatherv function is like the gatherv(byte[], int, byte[], int[], int[], int), except that all processes receive the result, instead of just the root. The block of data that is sent from the jth process is received by every process and placed in the jth block of the buffer rRecvBuf. These blocks do not all have to be the same size.
      参数:
      aSendBuf - The data array to be sent to all processes in the group. The number of the elements in the buffer are specified in the aSendCount and the data type will be detected automatically. Each element in the buffer corresponds to a process in the group.
      aSendCount - The number of elements in the buffer that is specified in the sendbuf parameter. If sendcount is zero, the data part of the message is empty.
      rRecvBuf - The data array that is received from each process. The number of the elements in the buffer are specified in the aRecvCounts parameters and the data type will be detected automatically.
      aRecvCounts - The number of data elements from each communicator process in the receive buffer.
      aDispls - The location, relative to the recvbuf parameter, of the data from each communicator process.

      public void gatherv(byte[] aSendBuf, int aSendCount, byte[] rRecvBuf, int[] aRecvCounts, int[] aDispls, int aRoot) throws MPIException
      Gathers variable data from all members of a group to one member. The gatherv function adds flexibility to the gather(byte[], int, byte[], int, int) function by allowing a varying count of data from each process.
      参数:
      aSendBuf - The data array to be sent to the root process.
      aSendCount - The number of elements in the buffer that is specified in the sendbuf parameter. If sendcount is zero, the data part of the message is empty.
      rRecvBuf - The data array on the root process that is received from each process. It includes data that is sent by the root process. This parameter is significant only at the root process. The recvbuf parameter is ignored for all non-root processes.
      aRecvCounts - The number of elements that is received from each process. Each element in the array corresponds to the rank of the sending process. If the count is zero, the data part of the message is empty. This parameter is significant only at the root process.
      aDispls - The location, relative to the recvbuf parameter, of the data from each communicator process. The data that is received from process j is placed into the receive buffer of the root process offset displs[j] elements from the sendbuf pointer.

      In the recvbuf, recvcounts, and displs parameter arrays, the nth element of each array refers to the data that is received from the nth communicator process.

      This parameter is significant only at the root process.

      aRoot - The rank of the receiving process within the specified communicator.
      抛出:
      MPIException
